itemDescription: footballer with Small Heath in the 1890s

wikipedia_page.main: George Smith (1868 – after 1890) was an English professional footballer who played in the Football Alliance for Small Heath. Smith, who was born in Birmingham, played his only league game for the club on 31 March 1891 in a 4–0 defeat at Sunderland Albion; he only played because regular left half Ted Devey missed the train.
